{"about_the_game":"<h2 class=\"bb_tag\">Real-time Physics For Maya 2020</h2><br>Animate like it's 1999, or leverage full-body dynamics to automate the vast majority of overlapping animation that even respond to changes in environment and interacts with other characters.<br><br>Ragdoll enables animators to work directly with live physics in their character rigs, at very little overhead and tight integration with kinematics.<br><br><img class=\"bb_img\" src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/1467930/extras/activeanimation2.gif?t=1609224981\" /><br><br>You can steer a simulated character with regular keyframe animation, like the above where the blue provides target poses and the colorful ragdoll obeys.<br><br><img class=\"bb_img\" src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/1467930/extras/mechanical.gif?t=1609224981\" /><br><br>The collision detection and constraints are stable and accurate enough to produce mathematical models, like this Reuleaux Triangle contraption.<br><br><img class=\"bb_img\" src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/1467930/extras/mgirl.gif?t=1609224981\" /><br><br>You can use it for cloth too, any overlapping animation will do just fine.<br><br><img class=\"bb_img\" src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/1467930/extras/muscle.gif?t=1609224981\" /><br><br>Including the kind of overlapping animation taking place internally, like muscles, fat and tendons.<br><br>I could go on, but you should really try it for yourself. Enjoy!","background":"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/1467930/page_bg_generated_v6b.jpg?t=1609224981","background_raw":"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/1467930/page.bg.jpg?t=1609224981","capsule_image":"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/1467930/capsule_231x87.jpg?t=1609224981","capsule_imagev5":"https://sha